  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Disaster risk reduction in Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNESCO and the CGMW supported geoscientists to produce the first Seismotectonic Map of Africa. The high density of historical and present earthquakes on the map illustrates clearly some of the major tectonic hotspots in Africa (e.g., East African Rift Valley). The map was the first landmark towards more detailed regional assessment as monitoring and mitigation tool, as well as basis seismic and geodetic networks for warning systems. This activity is a step further toward this goal with focus on Earthquake hazard assessment and modeling in the East African region. In addition, the Lake Chad basin, another disaster-prone region is a serious concern as result of Climate Change and even insecurity. The activity will also contribute to the efforts of the global community in this region.</narrative>
  </description>
